NAME finances
SAAS FINANCIAL MODELING & METRICS
A SaaS business is a math machine. If you don't know your numbers, you're guessing. This skill makes unit economics legible — MRR, CAC, LTV, churn, burn rate — clear enough to make decisions, rigorous enough to be trusted. 
CPS
A SaaS business is a math machine. If you don't know your numbers, you're guessing. Unit economics tell the truth about your business long before your bank account does. The only financial model that matters for a solo founder is one that fits on a single spreadsheet and gets updated monthly. Revenue is vanity. Margin is sanity. Cash flow is reality. Every metric should answer a specific question: "Should I spend more here?" or "Is this working?" 
